### Producer - Virtual Topic (topic:orders)
### Both consumer-alpha-1 and consumer-beta receive every message independently via their own durable queues
### (Consumer.consumer-alpha-1.VirtualTopic.orders and Consumer.consumer-beta.VirtualTopic.orders)
### consumer-beta also receives a copy via queue:all_events when sendToAllEventsQueue is true

### Post JSON (current format) - sendToAllEventsQueue: true
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "topic:orders",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": true,
  "format": "JSON_CURRENT",
  "messageType": "ORDER_PLACED",
  "data": {
    "orderId": "123",
    "total": 49.99
  }
}

### Post JSON (legacy format) - sendToAllEventsQueue: true
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "topic:orders",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": true,
  "format": "JSON_LEGACY",
  "messageType": "ORDER_PLACED",
  "data": {
    "orderId": "456",
    "total": 19.99
  }
}

### Post JSON (echoed current format)
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "topic:orders",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "format": "JSON_ECHOED_CURRENT",
  "messageType": "ORDER_PLACED",
  "data": {
    "orderId": "789",
    "total": 99.99
  }
}

### Post JSON (echoed legacy format)
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "topic:orders",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "format": "JSON_ECHOED_LEGACY",
  "messageType": "ORDER_PLACED",
  "data": {
    "orderId": "101",
    "total": 9.99
  }
}

### Post XML
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "topic:orders",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "format": "XML",
  "data": "<order><id>123</id></order>"
}

### Post TEXT
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "topic:orders",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "format": "TEXT",
  "data": "plain text order message"
}

### Post BYTES
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "topic:orders",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "format": "BYTES",
  "data": "bytes order message"
}

### Post JSON with conflicting types (triggers VerifyException in MessageTypeParser)
### Sets both the current-format messageType and the legacy metaData.type to different values.
### Watch consumer logs (docker compose logs -f consumer-alpha-1) for the failure and recovery cycle.
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "topic:orders",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "format": "JSON_CONFLICTING_TYPES",
  "messageType": "ORDER_PLACED",
  "data": {
    "orderId": "789",
    "total": 29.99
  }
}

### Producer - Plain JMS Topic (fixedtopic:announcements)
### Both consumer-alpha-1 and consumer-beta receive every message (fan-out)

### Post JSON to plain JMS topic
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "fixedtopic:announcements",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "format": "JSON_CURRENT",
  "messageType": "SYSTEM_NOTICE",
  "data": {
    "message": "Scheduled maintenance at midnight"
  }
}

### Producer - Regular Queue (queue:notifications)
### Competing consumers: each message delivered to exactly one of alpha or beta

### Post a single notification
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "queue:notifications",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "format": "JSON_CURRENT",
  "messageType": "USER_NOTIFICATION",
  "data": {
    "userId": "42",
    "message": "Your order has shipped"
  }
}

### Post multiple notifications to observe competing consumer behavior
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "queue:notifications",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "count": 10,
  "format": "JSON_CURRENT",
  "messageType": "USER_NOTIFICATION",
  "data": {
    "userId": "42",
    "message": "Your order has shipped"
  }
}

### Producer - DLQ Testing (queue:poison_pill)
### No consumer; messages expire after 30s TTL and move to ActiveMQ.DLQ

### Post to poison pill queue
POST http://localhost:8080/produce
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "destination": "queue:poison_pill",
  "sendToAllEventsQueue": false,
  "format": "TEXT",
  "data": "this will expire"
}

### Consumer Alpha - Received Messages (port 8081)

### Get all messages received by consumer-alpha-1
GET http://localhost:8081/received

### Get messages received by consumer-alpha-1 filtered by destination
GET http://localhost:8081/received?destination=topic:orders

### Get announcements received by consumer-alpha-1
GET http://localhost:8081/received?destination=fixedtopic:announcements

### Clear messages received by consumer-alpha-1
DELETE http://localhost:8081/received

### Consumer Alpha-2 - Received Messages (port 8082)
### Same serviceName as alpha-1; compare with alpha-1 to verify virtual topic competing consumer behavior

### Get all messages received by consumer-alpha-2
GET http://localhost:8082/received

### Get orders received by consumer-alpha-2 (should be disjoint from alpha-1's orders)
GET http://localhost:8082/received?destination=topic:orders

### Clear messages received by consumer-alpha-2
DELETE http://localhost:8082/received

### Consumer Beta - Received Messages (port 8083)

### Get all messages received by consumer-beta
GET http://localhost:8083/received

### Get orders received by consumer-beta (virtual topic - should match consumer-alpha-1's orders)
GET http://localhost:8083/received?destination=topic:orders

### Get messages received by consumer-beta filtered by destination
GET http://localhost:8083/received?destination=queue:notifications

### Get announcements received by consumer-beta
GET http://localhost:8083/received?destination=fixedtopic:announcements

### Clear messages received by consumer-beta
DELETE http://localhost:8083/received

### DLQ Management
### Both endpoints purge the same ActiveMQ.DLQ on the broker - use either

### Purge the DLQ (via consumer-alpha-1)
DELETE http://localhost:8081/dlq

### Purge the DLQ (via consumer-beta)
DELETE http://localhost:8083/dlq

### Health Checks

### Producer health check (includes ActiveMQ Producer Stats and dead-letter-queue)
GET http://localhost:8090/healthcheck

### Consumer-alpha-1 health check (includes ActiveMQ Consumer Stats and dead-letter-queue)
GET http://localhost:8091/healthcheck

### Consumer-alpha-2 health check (includes ActiveMQ Consumer Stats and dead-letter-queue)
GET http://localhost:8092/healthcheck

### Consumer-beta health check (includes ActiveMQ Consumer Stats)
GET http://localhost:8093/healthcheck
